Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @Sweet Potato{2} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Pop the @British Chicken Breasts{2} onto another baking tray, drizzle with @oil{} and season.

When the oven is hot, roast the sweet potato on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Roast the chicken on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop the sliced pepper, onion and garlic onto another baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and slightly charred, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While everything roasts, zest and halve the @Lime{1}.

Trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

Halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a #cutting board{} and chop into 1cm chunks.

Tear the @Ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks.

When the sweet potato has 10 mins remaining, remove the tray from the oven and add the croutons alongside. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Return the tray to the oven and bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the avocado chunks into a large #bowl{} with the lime zest and juice, @Honey{15%g} and @Olive Oil{2%tbsp} for the dressing.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop into a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well.

When everything's ready, add the roasted sweet potato, croutons, pepper, onion and sliced baby gem to the avocado bowl and toss to combine. Cut the chicken widthways into 2cm slices.

Share the salad between your #bowls{}, then top with the chicken slices and crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{50%g} to finish.

Enjoy!